**Problem description:**
System.Drawing.ImageConverter cannot convert from System.Drawing.Icon

**Actual behavior:** <!-- callstack for crashes / exceptions -->
System.Drawing.ImageConverter cannot convert from System.Drawing.Icon, and the value of the result_obj is null.
![ImageConverterIssue(Actual)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/18568603/57668656-91ee3900-763a-11e9-9e13-e141412b1f07.png)

**Expected behavior:**
System.Drawing.ImageConverter can convert from System.Drawing.Icon, the value of the result_obj isn’t null.
![ImageConverterIssue(Expected)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/18568603/57668661-94e92980-763a-11e9-9b76-c43937ed64a7.png)

**Minimal repro:**
1.	Create a Winforms .NET Core app.
2.	Add following code into Form.cs file.
   public Form1()
   {
    InitializeComponent();

    Icon test_Icon = Icon;
    myObj = new ImageConverter();
    Object result_obj = myObj.ConvertFrom(test_Icon);

    }
    protected System.Drawing.ImageConverter myObj = null;
3.	Make a breakpoint at this code line: Object result_obj = myObj.ConvertFrom(test_Icon);
4.	Run the app.

